Class RequestTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • <any>
      • ca.ualberta.cs.unter.modeltest.RequestTest

  • public class RequestTest
extends <any>
    Unit test cases for request model Since the controller class are designed to be as thick as possible, all business logic are inside the model class, which fits the MVC pattern. Therefore, it's pretty much no need to test controller class.

      • testUpdateRequest

        public void testUpdateRequest()
        Test update request. Once the request is modified, created, this method would be called to update request to the server. This test covers all update method for the rest of tests. In other word, no need to implement UpdateRequestTask in the rest of the test cases. Generally, the interaction with databae or server should be mocked up in the unittest (waste of resource, and possbility to mess up the production environment). Also, this test is not guarantee to pass.
